summary: Verify that a minimal AIB image boots successfully and passes basic runtime checks
description: |
  Builds a minimal Automotive Image Builder (AIB) bootc image and verifies that it boots correctly in a QEMU virtual
  machine.   The test monitors the serial console output to ensure the system reaches the expected boot target and that
  basic   post-boot checks (dmesg, SELinux, and systemd) all pass successfully.

  Test inputs:
    Custom AIB manifest defining a minimal bootable image

  Expected results:
    - PASS: All tests PASSED.

  Results location:
    output.txt

require:
  - qemu-kvm
  - expect
  - socat
duration: 60m
tag: [virt-required]
